<HEAD>Villagers Attack Police Station After Shooting Death</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Angry relatives of a robbery suspect police had
shot and killed ransacked the police headquarters in a southern
town, an official newspaper reported today.
   The rioters stormed the building before dawn May 21 in Jiaxi
Township, Guangdong province, breaking desks, a television set and
burning or smashing eight police motorcycles, the China Daily said.
   For more than an hour before dispersing, the intruders chased
police, stole 200 bullets, burned police uniforms and seized
documents and bicycles, the report said.
   It did not say how many villagers took part in the attack, but
said it was led by the father and brothers of Li Huaihe, the
shooting victim.
   Li was shot by police earlier that night while resisting arrest
after committing a robbery, the daily reported.
   It said the rioters caused about $51,000 in damage.
