<HEAD>Candidate's Wife Recovering</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Kitty Dukakis, wife of Democratic presidential
front-runner Michael Dukakis, was recuperating at Massachusetts
General Hospital today from spinal surgery she underwent last week.
   Mrs. Dukakis, 51, is ``doing splendidly on all fronts,'' Dr.
Nicholas T. Zervas, chief of neurology at the hospital, said Sunday.
``She's in splendid spirits.''
   Mrs. Dukakis had surgery Friday to remove two herniated discs in
her neck that were pressing dangerously on her spinal cord.
   Dukakis visited his wife at her hospital room on Sunday, and the
two strolled in the hospital corridor, hospital spokesman Martin
Bander said.
   After the visit, Dukakis returned to campaigning. He had stops in
New Jersey and then was flying to California. The two states hold
the final races of the Democratic primary season on Tuesday.
   The Massachusetts governor told reporters Sunday his wife had
some pain in her hip, where doctors removed bone for grafting, and
was walking with the support of a walker.
   Doctors have said Mrs. Dukakis probably would be hospitalized for
up to two weeks.
   Meanwhile, Mrs. Dukakis was receiving messages from well-wishers
who included some of her husband's former rivals for the Democratic
nomination.
   Mrs. Dukakis received a potted plant from Jesse Jackson. Jackson
remains an active Democratic candidate.
