<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Lyeth Killed,0095</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Winery Founder Killed In Plane Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GEYSERVILLE, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The founder of a small winery,
performing aerobatic stunts for family and friends at a picnic, was
killed when his plane crashed and burned.
   Munro Lyeth Jr., 45, founder of the Lyeth Winery, died inside the
single-engine plane when it caught fire Sunday in a vineyard near
his home.
   The Federal Aviation Administration is investigating the crash.
   Lyeth founded Lyeth Winery in 1981. He sold it this year, but
retained the vineyard. The winery produced about 20,000 bottles
annually.
</TEXT>
