<HEAD>Man Dies After Parachuting Off Hotel Roof</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MYRTLE BEACH, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who parachuted from the roof of a
23-story oceanfront hotel died after he was blown into the side of
another hotel, police said.
   Marlen Wade Burford, 28, of Titusville, Fla., died of injuries
sustained in the accident Sunday night, a police statement said.
   Police said today they were trying to locate a second man who
also parachuted from the Palace Resort Hotel but apparently landed
safely.
   High winds apparently carried Burford into the wall at the
Landmark Hotel next to the Palace Resort Hotel, Horry County Coroner
Gene Johnson said.
   An autopsy was being performed, Johnson said.
