<HEAD>Salvadoran President Duarte Scheduled For Surgery Tuesday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Salvadoran President Jose Napoleon Duarte has
decided to undergo exploratory surgery Tuesday to determine the
extent of the malignancy in his stomach and liver, a Walter Reed
Army Medical Center spokesman said Monday.
   The procedure, called an exploratory laparotomy, allows surgeons
to examine closely a patient's condition and remove some or all of
the diseased tissue, according to Pete Esker, medical center
spokesman.
   The 62-year-old Duarte, who is listed in ``guarded but stable''
condition, has been hospitalized since last week.
