to Europe later this summer for the annual Reforger exercise, the
Pentagon said Monday.
   The exercise, designed each year to demonstrate America's ability
to reinforce its NATO allies in Europe in the event of a war, will
begin with soldiers and equipment being transported by air and sea
to Belgium and West Germany, the Pentagon said.
   ``Major ground maneuvers will feature Exercise Certain Challenge
in September,'' the Pentagon added.
   ``Nearly 97,700 soldiers will participate, including 75,000
Americans; 17,500 Germans and 5,200 Canadians. Certain Challenge
will be held primarily in the German states of Baden Wuerttemberg
and Bavaria.''
