<DOCNO> AP880606-0130 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-06-06-88 1541EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r a AM-UpATree     06-06 0230</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Up A Tree,0234</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Stuck in a Tree Flees At Sound of Sirens</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CARY, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Firefighters have been known to rescue cats
from trees, so a caller to the town's emergency communications
center figured it was the logical place to turn for a man up a tree.
   Still, the dispatchers at first weren't sure they heard right,
said Tina Como.
   ``They said, `Do you get cats out of trees?' And we said, `No.'
Then they asked, `Do you get people out of trees?'''
   According to the dispatcher, a man apparently climbed a tall tree
Saturday afternoon and was afraid to get down, so somebody phoned
for help.
   ``I assume he was getting his cat out of the tree,'' Ms. Como
said. After she and other dispatchers got over what she described as
``a case of the giggles,'' they dispatched the Cary Rescue Squad and
the Cary Volunteer Fire Department.
   ``We figured you'd get a man out of the tree the same way you'd
get a cat out of a tree _ put a bowl of food out and wait for him to
come down,'' she said.
   After the caller phoned back to report the man had gotten down by
himself, the dispatchers recalled the firefighters.
   ``I guess he heard those sirens and decided he didn't want to be
embarrassed,'' Ms. Como said. ``He probably let go.''
</TEXT>
