<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Bear Recall,140</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Toycraft Stuffed Bears Recalled</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 9,000 Toycraft stuffed bears are being
recalled because their eyes and nose could come off and pose a
choking hazard for children, the Consumer Product Safety Commission
announced Monday.
   One child died of asphyxiation after the plastic nose from one of
the bears became lodged in her larynx, the commission reported.
   The recall covers stuffed bears with labels identifying the maker
as ``Toycraft Industries Inc., Brooklyn, N.Y.'' and stating
``Stuffed Toys for Tots and Teens.''
   The bears are 26 inches tall, nine inches across the chest and
come in assorted colors. They sold for about $6.
   The commission urged parents to take the bears from children and
return them to the store where purchased for a full refund.
   Persons needing more information can contact Toycraft at
1-718-788-2900 or the safety commission at 1-800-638-2772.
</TEXT>
