<2ND_LINE>AM-Lions Escape,0209</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lions Escape From Circus Ring, Maul to Death Young Sisters</HEAD>
<DATELINE>RIO DE JANEIRO, Brazil (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three lions broke through a wooden
fence during a circus in southeastern Brazil and mauled to death two
young children, police said Monday.
   The accident happened during a performance Saturday of the
Hungaro Circus in the town of Colonel Fabriciano, 335 miles
northeast of Rio de Janeiro.
   Osman Canela, the police chief, said 2-year-old Maira da Silva
and her 5-year-old sister, Marina, were sitting in the front row of
the wooden bleachers when the lions broke from their trainer and
burst through the fence separating the ring from the stands.
   One lion grabbed Maira by the head and a second mauled Marina, he
said.
   A circus performer managed to capture a third lion, Canela said.
   Marina was killed instantly, and Maira died when she arrived at
the hospital, according to Rio's Jornal do Brasil newspaper.
   The girls had gone to the show with their aunt and uncle, who
were both injured trying to save their nieces, according to the
newspapers. The couple's own two children were not injured in the
attack.
   Canela said the circus owners would be charged in connection with
the deaths.
</TEXT>
