<HEAD>Dukakis Picks Up Bulk of Kentucky Delegation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FRANKFORT, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gov. Wallace Wilkinson of Kentucky endorsed
Democratic front-runner Michael Dukakis for the party's presidential
nomination Monday and said that almost all of the Kentucky
delegation to the national convention will follow his lead.
   The switch means 41 delegates, most of whom were previously
committed to dropout candidate Albert Gore Jr., will jump to the
Dukakis camp. As it now stands, all but six of Kentucky's 67
delegates to the July convention will back the Massachusetts
governor.
   The remaining delegates are committed to Jesse Jackson.
   Wilkinson, who had earlier pledged his support to Gore, said Gore
had not formally released him from that support but did not object
to the switch in allegiance.
   The change came as the Dukakis camp was hoping to muster enough
delegates to assure a first-ballot nomination at the convention in
Atlanta.
