<HEAD>Quotes From the Presidential Campaign Trail</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are some comments Monday from the
presidential campaign trail:
   
   GEORGE BUSH, saying he'll probably be differing more with the
Reagan administration as the presidential campaign continues:``As I
become the standard bearer of this party, I'm going to be saying,
without regard to current administration position, here's what
George Bush feels ... here's what my aspirations for the country
are.''
   
   MICHAEL DUKAKIS, on what he expects from Jesse Jackson this fall:
``If the tables were reversed and he was on his way to the
nomination and I was the runner-up, I'd expect to be deeply
involved. ... I'd try to bring my people into this. I'd be as much
service to the ticket as I possibly could. I'm confident he will be
that kind of person.''
   
   JESSE JACKSON, warning he'll take Dukakis to task at the
Democratic National Convention if the Massachusetts governor fails
to change his position on South Africa: ``If he will not bend on
that matter, we'll simply meet on the floor at Atlanta. ... The
matter needs to be resolved in the committee or in platform hearings
or on the convention floor.''
