<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Spain-Killing     06-06 0126</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Spain-Killing,0128</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Discotheque Owner Killed, Basque Separatists Suspected</HEAD>
<DATELINE>EIGOIBAR, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three gunmen believed to be Basque
separatists fatally shot the owner of a discotheque Monday evening
in this town near San Sebastian, police reported.
   Police quoted witnesses as saying Patxi Zabaleta, 40, was shot
down while walking in the street.
   Police said they believed the killing was the work of the
separatist group ETA, whose initials stand for ``Basque land and
liberty'' in the Basque language.
   ETA has claimed responsibility for the deaths of three policemen,
a retired general and a restaurant owner so far this year. Since it
began operating in 1968, the organization has claimed more than 600
deaths in its campaign for an independent nation in Spain's northern
Basque provinces.
</TEXT>
