<FILEID>AP-NR-06-06-88 0002EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>a a BC-SPE--Outdoors:Panfish-Cleaning     06-06 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-SPE--Outdoors: Panfish-Cleaning,0173</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BC-SPECIAL EDITION</HEAD>
<HEAD>OUTDOORS: With BC-Panfish</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BILL SCHULZ</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Cleaning your fish is as easy as 1, 2, 3, 4, 5,
according to fishing experts at Mariner Outboards. You need a sharp
fillet knife and a fish dressing pliers.
   Follow these steps:
   1 _ Hold the fish upright on its belly or lay on its side and
slice the head off at an angle, behind the gill covers.
   2 _ Lay the fish on its side and use a fillet knife to cut along
both sides of the anal and dorsal fins.
   3 _ Use the fish dressing pliers to pull out the fins, grasping
them from the rear and pulling forward. This also should remove the
entrails. Use a finger to pull out any remaining entrails.
   4 _ Grasp the skin at the top corner of each side with the fish
dressing pliers and peal it off.
   5 _ Cut off the tail and cook to your taste.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
