maintain, to erase the inflation worries and uncertainties about the
election outlook that had been depressing the market until last week.
   Macmillan Inc. climbed 2{ to 74. The Robert M. Bass Group raised
its takeover bid for the company from $64 a share to $73 a share.
   Avon Products fell 1[ to 22}. The company said late last week it
plans to sell its health-care operations and cut its annual dividend
from $2 a share to $1 a share.
   Among the blue-chip industrials, Ford Motor rose } to 50 and
American Express was up ] at 26|, while General Electric slipped \
to 42] and Pocter & Gamble fell 1\ to 76[.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks lost
.30 to 150.01. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index was up .34 at 301.22.
   Volume on the Big Board came to 123.24 million shares with an
hour to go.
